peru announc larg new gold find presid alan garcia said peru ha found gold deposit worth an estim 1.3 billion dlr in a jungl region near the ecuadorean border about 1,000 km north of here . he told report yesterday the deposit , locat at four site near the town of san ignasio , contain the equiv of 100 tonn of gold . garcia said the govern would soon instal a two mln dlr treatment plant at tomaqu . it will extract enough ore to provid an estim 25 mln dlr profit by the end of thi year , he ad . garcia said the other gold-bear deposit are locat at tamborapa , pachapidiana , and a zone between the cenepa and santiago river .